The last two times Bay tried to be dramatic or to make a movie with some substance we got Pain and Gain and Pearl Harbor, both of which were pretty bad movies.  Michael Bay is not a good director, even for his own genre. I know that he's tried to direct more dramatic films in the past, but he doesn't have the depth or the insight to helm such a project and from the look of the film it seems more like a propagandist cash grab For the 2016 election than it does a film that going to stand the test of time or be remembered fondly.   If Hollywood was going to do a Benghazi movie regardless of what year it was coming out, they needed a better director to handle such sensitive subject matter.  It kind of feels like It'll be Bay's Lone Survivor, where he'll show his own admiration for the armed forced, but also end up playing fast and loose with the facts and making more of a pro-American film than an accurate or complex analysis of the Benghazi attack.

text: This was Ok... If I was never in the military or in the Infantry, this would be an astounding Call of Duty style movie and I wouldn't know any better about inaccuracies. Using the many weapon systems used in the movie it just looks so Hollywood to see them depicted on screen. I know this wasn't meant to be an accurate "war movie" or anything but MBay could've had a weapons expert near by to say "this is how they work". Saving Private Ryan and Black Hawk Down were much more realistic. When an 80mm mortar goes off 5 ft from you, you don't get up and walk it off (you're probably dead), .50 bullets go through those thin walls (and roof of compound they were in) as if it were made of paper. 7.62mm rounds only work in a 240B even though the SAW gunners were strapped with 7.62(5.56 links are way smaller). It's hard as hell to hit anything outside of 25m with night vision and not use your PEQ-15 (they only used the PEQ-15 once to spot some targets). RPG rounds don't explode like 5 lbs of C4. It's really hard to shoot standing up unsupported with a SAW at targets in the dark that are 150+ meters away. Such a COD style movie lol.
